migratory birds can be seen crashing into the ground in Cuauhtémoc, Chihuahua.  The flock was located on Aldama Avenue and First Street, in the downtown area of ​​the city. 

Video recorded on Monday around 05:00. According to local media, the residents of the sector, seeing the strange behavior of the birds, spoke to the authorities. At least 100 dead migratory birds of the Yellow-headed Thrush (Xanthocephalus) species were found at the site.

The birds migrate from northern Canada to northern Mexico where they spend the winter. 

Sauce: https://abcnoticias.mx/nacional/2022/2/10/captan-momento-en-que-mueren-decenas-de-aves-en-chihuahua-156556.html</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PI9zsMD.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>sauce: https://twitter.com/CapitanFuria13/status/1491647836672303110

Discussion: https://www.reddit.com/r/WTF/comments/spfe99/huge_group_of_birds_falling_down_from_sky_what/hwfwq7l/

When raptors like peregrine falcons or merlins are chasing certain bird species like starlings, the prey species literally "flock" together into a huge group called a murmuration. The movement of the murmuration is controlled by something called "scale-free correlation". 

https://www.allaboutbirds.org/news/how-do-starling-flocks-create-those-mesmerizing-murmurations/

Basically, each bird reacts to the movement of the bird next to it, but there is no leader of the flock or central direction. So it is possible for a murmuration to flee so vigorously from a falcon on one side that the individual responses of the birds accumulate through the crowd to blow out the other side of the murmuration in a death dive. 

https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-wales-51880855

With behavior this complex, it's pretty common to have a glitch in the murmuration. It's generally fine...unless they happen to be very close to a solid object. But hey, easy pickings.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/6o5apyk</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[psuedon]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Untold History</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/gvrf3FM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lY0t1WZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bessie_Coleman #blackhistorymonth #aviator #untold #themoreyouknow</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gvrf3FM</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MartyIndependence]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>&quot;I started from the bottom&quot;</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/od8LKYf</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9Cn8MQ3.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/od8LKYf</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ButtBot9900]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>:)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/01MwJFW</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8heBVdO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/01MwJFW</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mfrybeasley]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>When everyone replies to the top comment right after the post goes viral.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/WPyxgWx</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Fb7AluE.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>fun stuff…absurdly long week…send something fucking great.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/WPyxgWx</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[deafkitten]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Nothing by Dr. King said inspired this.</title><link>h